      • forceFetchAndroidClient

        public static void forceFetchAndroidClient​(boolean forceFetchAndroidClientValue)
        Enable or disable the fetch of the Android client for all stream types.

        By default, the fetch of the Android client will be made only on videos, in order to reduce data usage, because available streams of the Android client will be almost equal to the ones available on the WEB client: you can get exclusively a 48kbps audio stream and a 3GPP very low stream (which is, most of times, a 144p8 stream).

        Parameters:
        forceFetchAndroidClientValue - whether to always fetch the Android client and not only for videos

      • forceFetchIosClient

        public static void forceFetchIosClient​(boolean forceFetchIosClientValue)
        Enable or disable the fetch of the iOS client for all stream types.

        By default, the fetch of the iOS client will be made only on livestreams, in order to get an HLS manifest with separated audio and video which has also an higher replay time (up to one hour, depending of the content instead of 30 seconds with non-iOS clients).

        Enabling this option will allow you to get an HLS manifest also for regular videos, which contains resolutions up to 1080p60.

        Parameters:
        forceFetchIosClientValue - whether to always fetch the iOS client and not only for livestreams
